==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Parkeria
<hw>Par*ke"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[NL. So
named from <person>W. K. <etsep>Parker</etsep></person>, a British
zoologist.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of large arenaceous
fossil Foraminifera found in the Cretaceous rocks. The species are
globular, or nearly so, and are of all sizes up to that of a tennis
ball.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parkeriaceae</ent>⟦br⟧
